        |- trigger_multiple
        |- trigger_use
		|- trigger_use_touch
        |- trigger_hurt
		|- trigger_damage ( sort of )
		
	
	**NOTES
		- setHintString doesn't work so you must use setHintStringTrigger.
		- setCursorHint doesn't work so you must use setCursorHintTrigger.

